DESCRIPTION:THIS AGREEMENT IS TO AN ELIGIBLE STATE OR TRIBE TO IMPLEMENT A PROGRAM TO PROVIDE DRINKING WATER PROGRAM ASSISTANCE TO UNDERSERVED, SMALL AND DISADVANTAGED COMMUNITIES. FUNDS ARE TO CARRY OUT PROJECTS AND ACTIVITIES NEEDED FOR PUBLIC WATER SYSTEMS TO COMPLY WITH THE SAFE DRINKING WATER ACT, PROGRAMS TO PROVIDE HOUSEHOLD WATER QUALITY TESTING, AND ACTIVITIES FOR A STATE TO RESPOND TO A DRINKING WATER CONTAMINANT.ACTIVITIES:FUNDING PROVIDED UNDER THIS GRANT TO DNRC, (THE ELIGIBLE RECIPIENT), WILL BE SUB AWARDED TO SMALL, UNDERSERVED COMMUNITIES FOR INVESTMENT IN PUBLIC WATER SYSTEM UPGRADES. THESE UPGRADES ARE NECESSARY TO MEET SDWA REQUIREMENTS FOR WIIN GRANT FUNDS AND CAN MEET THE NON-FEDERAL MATCH REQUIREMENTS IN THE WIIN GRANT. DEQ IS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE IMPLEMENTATION OF THE SDWA WHICH INCLUDES THE REVIEW AND APPROVAL OF MODIFICATIONS TO EXISTING OR PROPOSED PUBLIC WATER SUPPLY SYSTEMS AS WELL AS ENFORCEMENT OF THE PROVISIONS OF THE SDWA. DEQ WILL ALSO PROVIDE TECHNICAL EXPERTISE THROUGHOUT THE PLANNING AND CONSTRUCTION OF THE PROJECTS.SUBRECIPIENT: ACTIVITIES INCLUDE

- PLANNING AND DESIGN OF SYSTEM UPGRADES;
- CONSTRUCTION OF A NEW OR IMPROVED TREATMENT SYSTEM;
- REPLACEMENT OR CONSTRUCTION OF TRANSMISSION OR DISTRIBUTION SYSTEMS;
- UPGRADES TO STORAGE;
- CONSOLIDATION OF COMMUNITIES;
- HOUSEHOLD WATER QUALITY TESTING, INCLUDING TESTING FOR UNREGULATED CONTAMINANTS;
- ASSISTANCE TO INCREASE TECHNICAL, MANAGERIAL, AND FINANCIAL CAPACITY; AND
- DRINKING WATER CONTAMINATION RESPONSE EFFORTS. . DIRECT BENEFICIARIES OF THIS ASSISTANCE AGREEMENT INCLUDE RESIDENTS OF THE STATE OF MONTANA.  OUTCOMES:ELIGIBLE PROJECTS - 1459A LIST
SUB AWARDS WILL BE USED TO SUPPORT PROJECTS AND ACTIVITIES IN UNDERSERVED, SMALL AND DISADVANTAGED COMMUNITIES THAT ARE NECESSARY FOR A PUBLIC WATER SYSTEM TO COMPLY WITH THE SDWA. SPECIFIC ACTIVITIES WILL INCLUDE:
- PLANNING AND DESIGN OF SYSTEM UPGRADES;
- CONSTRUCTION OF A NEW OR IMPROVED TREATMENT SYSTEM;
- REPLACEMENT OR CONSTRUCTION OF TRANSMISSION OR DISTRIBUTION SYSTEMS;
- UPGRADES TO STORAGE;
- CONSOLIDATION OF COMMUNITIES;
- HOUSEHOLD WATER QUALITY TESTING, INCLUDING TESTING FOR UNREGULATED CONTAMINANTS;
- ASSISTANCE TO INCREASE TECHNICAL, MANAGERIAL, AND FINANCIAL CAPACITY; AND
- DRINKING WATER CONTAMINATION RESPONSE EFFORTS.

THE OUTPUT EXPECTED FROM THE PROJECTS THAT WILL BE FUNDED WITH THIS GRANT IS AN INCREASE IN COMPLIANCE OF PUBLIC WATER SYSTEMS IN SMALL AND DISADVANTAGED COMMUNITIES WITH NATIONAL DRINKING WATER REGULATIONS.

EXPECTED OUTCOMES FROM THE ACTIVITIES DESCRIBED IN THIS WORKPLAN INCLUDE 1) A REDUCTION IN THE NUMBER OF PUBLIC WATER SYSTEMS OUT OF COMPLIANCE WITH HEALTH-BASED STANDARDS IN SMALL AND DISADVANTAGED COMMUNITIES, 2) IMPROVED PERFORMANCE OF DRINKING WATER PLANTS IN SMALL AND DISADVANTAGED COMMUNITIES, AND 3) AN INCREASE IN THE NUMBER OF PUBLIC WATER SYSTEMS IN SMALL AND DISADVANTAGED COMMUNITIES THAT WILL BE ABLE TO PROVIDE THE CONSTITUENCY OF THE COMMUNITY WITH SAFE DRINKING WATER.

DESCRIPTION:THIS AGREEMENT IS TO AN ELIGIBLE STATE OR TRIBE TO IMPLEMENT A PROGRAM TO PROVIDE DRINKING WATER PROGRAM ASSISTANCE TO UNDERSERVED, SMALL AND DISADVANTAGED COMMUNITIES. FUNDS ARE TO CARRY OUT PROJECTS AND ACTIVITIES NEEDED FOR PUBLIC WATER SYSTEMS TO COMPLY WITH THE SAFE DRINKING WATER ACT, PROGRAMS TO PROVIDE HOUSEHOLD WATER QUALITY TESTING, AND ACTIVITIES FOR A STATE TO RESPOND TO A DRINKING WATER CONTAMINANT.ACTIVITIES:THIS PROJECT INVOLVES THE REPLACEMENT OF AUGUSTA WATERWORKS WELL #7, WHICH IS CONTAMINATED WITH NITRATE. THE PROJECT INVOLVES BRINGING THE NEW REPLACEMENT WELL ON-LINE AND INCLUDES INSTALLATION AND CONSTRUCTION OF THE FOLLOWING: 

-WELL PUMP AND CONTROLS; 
-NEW PUMPHOUSE; DISCHARGE PIPING; 
-AERATOR AND CHEMICAL FEED SYSTEMS; 
-CLEARWELL/DETENTION TANK; 
-BOOSTER PUMP WITH DISCHARGE PIPING; 
-IRON FILTRATION SYSTEM; 
-DISCHARGE PIPING CONNECTING WELLHOUSE TO EXISTING DISTRIBUTION SYSTEM; 
-BACKWASH TANK; AND 
-AUXILIARY POWER GENERATOR.  SUBRECIPIENT:THE ENTIRE GRANT WILL BE A SUBAWARD AND INVOLVES THE REPLACEMENT OF AUGUSTA WATERWORKS WELL #7, WHICH IS CONTAMINATED WITH NITRATE. THE PROJECT INVOLVES BRINGING THE NEW REPLACEMENT WELL ON-LINE AND INCLUDES INSTALLATION AND CONSTRUCTION OF THE FOLLOWING: 

-WELL PUMP AND CONTROLS; 
-NEW PUMPHOUSE; DISCHARGE PIPING; 
-AERATOR AND CHEMICAL FEED SYSTEMS; 
-CLEARWELL/DETENTION TANK; 
-BOOSTER PUMP WITH DISCHARGE PIPING; 
-IRON FILTRATION SYSTEM; 
-DISCHARGE PIPING CONNECTING WELLHOUSE TO EXISTING DISTRIBUTION SYSTEM; 
-BACKWASH TANK; AND 
-AUXILIARY POWER GENERATOR.  OUTCOMES:DELIVERABLE INCLUDE AN ENGINEERING REPORT, PLANS AND SPECIFICATIONS, AND A CONTRACT FOR CONSTRUCTION BETWEEN AUGUSTA WATERWORKS AND LOWEST APPROPRIATE BIDDER. THE OUTCOME OF THIS PROJECT IS THE AUGUSTA WATERWORKS SYSTEM WILL RETURN TO COMPLIANCE WITH THE NATIONAL PRIMARY DRINKING WATER STANDARDS. THE CUSTOMERS OF THE AUGUSTA WATERWORKS WILL ENJOY THE BENEFITS OF THIS PROJECT BY RECEIVING CLEAN AND SAFE DRINKING WATER.
